      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 180,
      "message": "Ah, yes, I tried that earlier, however the code analysis tool complained about negetive method usage. \nFor example., \npublic boolean isClientNameValid() {\n  return !(StringUtils.isBlank(clienName));\n}\n\n... in the JerseyClient...\nif (!isClientValid()) {\n  throw new IllegalArgumentException(...);\n}\n\nIn this example the usage of this method is negetive context., hence we are doing 2 negetive operations (one in the method and 2nd in the usage of this method).. which is expensive., \nhence code analysis tool suggest to not do this., \nHence I choose this kind of method for some of the methods ., \nthere are some with isValid kind of., but thats because of their usage., \n\nThanks, please let me know ur view.,",
